4. LEGAL BASIS AND JURISDICTION (Brazilian Law)
------------------------------------------------
This License is governed by and construed in accordance with the laws of the
Federative Republic of Brazil. Any dispute arising out of or in connection with
this License shall be subject to the exclusive jurisdiction of the courts of
the State of São Paulo, Brazil.

The prohibitions set forth in Section 2 are supported by, and any violation
thereof shall constitute a breach of:

  • Lei nº 9.609, de 19 de fevereiro de 1998 ("Lei do Software")
    — Art. 1º: software is protected as an intellectual work of authorship.
    — Art. 2º: applicable copyright protections extend to software.
    — Art. 9º: the use of software by third parties requires express
      authorization by the rights holder, granted by license or assignment.
    — Art. 12: unauthorized reproduction, in whole or in part, for commercial
      purposes, constitutes a civil and criminal infringement.

  • Lei nº 9.610, de 19 de fevereiro de 1998 ("Lei de Direitos Autorais")
    — Art. 7º, XII: computer programs are expressly protected works.
    — Art. 28: the Author has the exclusive right to use, enjoy, and dispose
      of the work.
    — Art. 29: depends on the prior and express authorization of the Author
      any full or partial use of the work, including reproduction, distribution,
      translation, adaptation, and any form of economic exploitation.
    — Art. 46: provides a closed list of uses that do not constitute
      infringement (e.g., private transcription of short excerpts, accessibility
      uses) — commercial exploitation is NEVER among them.
    — Arts. 101–110: establish civil remedies, including seizure, damages, and
      profits disgorgement for infringement.

  • Decreto-Lei nº 2.848, de 7 de dezembro de 1940 ("Código Penal")
    — Art. 184, §1º: reproduction of intellectual work with intent of direct
      or indirect commercial gain, without the author's express authorization,
      is a criminal offense punishable with imprisonment of 2 (two) to 4 (four)
      years and a fine.
    — Art. 184, §2º: the same penalty applies to anyone who distributes,
      sells, offers, or keeps in deposit, for commercial purposes, a copy of
      intellectual work produced in violation of the author's rights.

By breaching this License — particularly its Section 2 — the infringer exposes
themselves to civil liability (under Lei 9.609/98 and Lei 9.610/98) AND
criminal prosecution (under Art. 184 of the Código Penal), in addition to any
immediate injunctive relief sought by the Author.


